research_municipality_step.notes: Woodbridge Township, New Jersey, operates under the Mayor-Council Plan (Plan F) of the Faulkner Act. The local government consists of a directly elected Mayor and a nine-member Township Council. Four council members are elected at-large, and five are elected from specific wards. The Mayor and Council members serve four-year terms. The roles of Council President and Vice President were determined based on a November 2025 council meeting roll call.
